ws |date=September 8, 1876 |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C05E2D81F3FE73BBC4053DFBF66838D669FDE |title=The Safe Burglary Case: Preparing for the trial \u2013 Witnesses for the defense summoned|newspaper=The New York Times }}\n*{{cite news |author=E.G.D. |title=The Pantaloon of the Senate: A Reminiscence of the Emma Mine Scandal |newspaper=The New York Times |date=October 9, 1893 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1893/10/09/109711163.pdf}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |last=Ackerman |first=Kenneth D. |title=The Gold Ring Jim Fisk, Jay Gould, and Black Friday, 1869 |publisher=Viral History Press, Inc. |location=[[Falls Church, Virginia|Falls Church]], [[Virginia]] |ref={{sfnRef|Ackerman}}|date=2011 |isbn=978-1-61945-013-4}}\n* {{cite book |last=Brands |first=H. W. |authorlink=H.W. Brands |title=The Man Who Saved The Union Ulysses S. Grant in War and Peace |publisher=Doubleday |location=New York |year=2012 |isbn=978-0-385-53241-9 |ref={{sfnRef|Brands 2012a}} |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/manwhosavedunion0000bran }} major scholarly biography\n* {{cite journal |last=Brands |first=H. W. |title=Presidents in Crisis: Grant Takes on the Klan |journal=American History |pages=42\u201347|date=December 2012 |ref={{sfnRef|Brands 2012b}}}}\n* Buenker, John D. and Joseph Buenker, eds. ''Encyclopedia of the Gilded Age and Progressive Era'' (2005). 1256 pp. in three volumes. 900 essays by 200 scholars\n* Donald, David Herbert. ''Charles Sumner and the Rights of Man'' (1970), Pulitzer Prize\u2013winning biography of Grant's enemy in the Senate\n* Fitzgerald, Michael W. ''Splendid Failure: Postwar Reconstruction in the American South.'' (2007) 234 pp.&nbsp;{{ISBN|978-1-56663-734-3}}\n* Foner, Eric. ''Reconstruction: America's Unfinished Revolution, 1863\u20131877'' (1988),  Pulitzer Prize\u2013winning synthesis from [[neoabolitionist]] perspective\n* Graber, Jennifer. \"\"If a War It May Be Called\" The Peace 