ers and writing by Grant, and the most important letters written to him.\n*[[James D. Richardson|Richardson, James]], ed. ''[[Compilation of the Messages and Papers of the Presidents]]'' (numerous editions, 1901\u201320), vol 7 contains most of Grant's official presidential public documents and messages to Congress\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29510 1869 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29511 1870 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29512 1871 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29513 1872 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29514 1873 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29515 1874 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29516 1875 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=29517 1876 State of the Union Message \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=25820 1869 Inaugural Address \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=25821 1873 Inaugural Address \u2013 Ulysses S. Grant]\n*{{cite book |last=Hackett |first=Frank Warren |title=Reminiscences of the Geneva Tribunal of Arbitration, 1872, the Alabama Claims |publisher=[[Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|Houghton Mifflin]] |location=New York City |oclc=2621753 |chapter=Chapter III: The Alabama Claims \u2013 The Treaty of Washington |pages=45\u201350 |year=1911 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=_n1DAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA45&dq=The+notoriety+gained+by+the+Alabama&cd=1#v=onepage&q=The%20notoriety%20gained%20by%20the%20Alabama |accessdate=January 30, 2010}}\n*{{cite book |last=McPherson |fir