es S. Grant and Hamilton Fish.\" in Edward O. Frantz, ed., '' A Companion to the Reconstruction Presidents 1865\u20131881'' (2014): 311+\n* {{cite book|ref=harv |last=McFeely |first=William S. |authorlink=William S. McFeely |title=Grant: A Biography |publisher=Norton |year=1981 |isbn=0-393-01372-3 |url=https://archive.org/details/grantbiography00mcfe }}, major scholarly biography\n* {{cite book |ref=harv |last=McFeely |first=William S. |editor1-last=Woodward |editor1-first=C. Vann |title=Responses of the Presidents to Charges of Misconduct |publisher=Delacorte Press |location=New York, New York |pages=133\u2013162 |year=1974 |isbn=0-440-05923-2 }}\n* Mantell, Martin E. ''Johnson, Grant, and the Politics of Reconstruction'' (1973) [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=89815306 online edition]\n* {{cite book |last=Nevins |first=Allan |authorlink=Allan Nevins |url=https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=94934148 |title=Hamilton Fish: The Inner History of the Grant Administration |location=New York |publisher=Dodd, Mead |year=1936 |volume=2 |asin=B00085BDXU |ref={{sfnRef|Nevins}}}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef|Patrick}} |last=Patrick |first=Rembert W. |title=The Reconstruction of the Nation |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=[[New York City|New York]] |year=1968 |isbn=0-195-01016-7}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |ref={{sfnRef|Paxson & Bach}} |year=1931 |title =Ulysses S. Grant |encyclopedia=[[Dictionary of American Biography]] |last1=Paxson |first1=Frederic Logan |last2=Bach |first2=Christian A. |volume=VII |pages=492\u2013501 |publisher=C. Scribner's Sons |location=New York |url=https://archive.org/stream/dictionaryofamer07ilamer#page/492/mode/2up}}\n* Perret, Geoffrey. ''Ulysses S. Grant: Soldier & President'' (2009). popular biography\n* Priest, Andrew. \"Thinking about Empire: The Administration of Ulysses S. Grant, Spanish Colonialism and the Ten Years' War in Cuba.\" ''Journal of American Studies'' (2014) 48#2 pp: 541\u2013558.\n* {{cite book |last=Rable |first=G