{"title_page": "Somethin' 'Bout a Truck", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\n| cover      = SBATKipMoore.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Kip Moore]]\n| album      = [[Up All Night (Kip Moore album)|Up All Night]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2011|09|26}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2011\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=36}}\n| label      = [[Universal Music Group Nashville|MCA Nashville]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Kip Moore|Dan Couch}}\n| producer   = [[Brett James]]\n| prev_title = [[Mary Was the Marrying Kind]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Beer Money]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\n\"'''Somethin' 'Bout a Truck'''\" is a song co-written and recorded by American [[country music]] artist [[Kip Moore]]. It was released in September 2011 as the first single from his debut album ''[[Up All Night (Kip Moore album)|Up All Night]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Duvall|first=Erin|title=Kip Moore, 'Up All Night' Album Coming in April|url=http://www.theboot.com/2012/03/02/kip-moore-up-all-night-album/|accessdate=March 3, 2012|publisher=The Boot|date=March 2, 2012}}</ref> Moore wrote this song with and Dan Couch.<ref>{{cite news|last=Conaway|first=Alanna|title=Kip Moore, \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 \u2013 Lyrics Uncovered|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck-lyrics/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|newspaper=Taste of Country|date=September 18, 2011}}</ref> It garnered positive reviews from critics who praised Moore's delivery for being able to elevate generic lyrics. \"Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\" reached number one on the US [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] [[Hot Country Songs]] chart, the only single in Moore's career to reach that peak to date. It also gave him his first and only top 40 hit on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], peaking at number 29. The song was certified 2x Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA), denoting sales of over two million units in the country. It also charted in Canada, peaking at number 33 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]]. Two accompanying music videos were made for the single, the official version by Roger Pistole and an acoustic version by Stephen Shepherd.\n\n==Content==\nMoore discussed the album in an interview with [[American Songwriter]]. He stated, \"I made a conscious effort on this record to try to capture the youthful spirit that we all have inside of us. So often people as they get older they feel like things have to change inside their spirit. We all have to mature and take on different responsibilities. I tried to really capture...that you don\u2019t have to let your soul die or spirit die. You can still keep that youthful way and still live that way.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Behind The Wheel: A Q&A With Kip Moore|url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2012/06/behind-the-wheel-a-qa-with-kip-moore/2/|last=Jewly|first=Jewly|publisher=[[American Songwriter]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe song is in a moderate tempo in the key of [[B major]]. Its accompaniment is [[open fifth]]s instead of chords, in a pattern of B5-E5-B5-F{{sharp}}5-B5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/scorchVPE.asp?ppn=SC0238407&|title='Somethin' 'Bout a Truck' sheet music|publisher=MusicNotes.com|accessdate=July 3, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nBilly Dukes of ''[[Taste of Country]]'' gave the song three stars out of five, saying that \"vocally, he's not a perfect match for this style, but he's able to overcome somewhat cliche lyrics to create a memorable single.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Dukes|first=Billy|title=Kip Moore, \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 \u2013 Song Review|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Taste of Country|date=September 13, 2011}}</ref> Kevin John Coyne of Country Universe gave the song a B+ grade, writing that Moore \"sounds like he's reveling in the pleasures that await him at the end of the week after forty hours at the factory,\" calling it \"a welcome change from those who sound like high schoolers who hit up that back country road on their way home from the mall.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Coyne|first=Kevin John|title=Single Review: Kip Moore, \"Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\"|url=http://www.countryuniverse.net/2012/01/22/single-review-kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Roughstock|date=January 22, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was directed by Roger Pistole and premiered in October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Dukes|first=Billy|title=Kip Moore Releases Simple and Sexy \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 Video|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck-video/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Taste of Country|date=October 25, 2011}}</ref> An acoustic music video was directed by Stephen Shepherd and premiered in June 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/kip-moore/742541/somethin-bout-a-truck-acoustic.jhtml|title=CMT : Videos : Kip Moore : Somethin' 'Bout A Truck (Acoustic)|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|accessdate=August 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\" debuted at number 51 on the U.S. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Country Songs]] chart for the week of October 22, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Morris|first=Edward|title=Scotty McCreery, Keith Urban Top This Week's Album, Songs Charts|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1672552/scotty-mccreery-keith-urban-top-this-weeks-album-songs-charts.jhtml|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|date=October 15, 2011}}</ref> It also debuted at number 89 on the U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100]] chart for the week of February 25, 2012. It also debuted at number 97 on [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart for the week of April 14, 2012.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2011\u201312)\n!align=\"center\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|33|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|29|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcountrysongs|1|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2012)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/hot-100-songs?begin=91&order=position|title=Best of 2012 - Hot 100 Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|96\n|-\n| US [[Hot Country Songs|Country Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/hot-country-songs | title=Best of 2012: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 12\n|-\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United States|artist=Kip Moore|title=Somethin%27 Bout a Truck|award=Platinum|number=2|certyear=2014|certmonth=12|relyear=2011|access-date=March 21, 2015}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kip Moore}}\n\n[[Category:2011 singles]]\n[[Category:2011 songs]]\n[[Category:Kip Moore songs]]\n[[Category:MCA Nashville Records singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Country Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Brett James]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kip Moore]]\n[[Category:Songs about cars]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\n| cover      = SBATKipMoore.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Kip Moore]]\n| album      = [[Up All Night (Kip Moore album)|Up All Night]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2011|09|26}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2011\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=36}}\n| label      = [[Universal Music Group Nashville|MCA Nashville]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Kip Moore|Dan Couch}}\n| producer   = [[Brett James]]\n| prev_title = [[Mary Was the Marrying Kind]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Beer Money]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n}}\n\n\"'''Somethin' 'Bout a Truck'''\" is a song co-written and recorded by American [[country music]] artist [[Kip Moore]]. It was released in September 2011 as the first single from his debut album ''[[Up All Night (Kip Moore album)|Up All Night]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Duvall|first=Erin|title=Kip Moore, 'Up All Night' Album Coming in April|url=http://www.theboot.com/2012/03/02/kip-moore-up-all-night-album/|accessdate=March 3, 2012|publisher=The Boot|date=March 2, 2012}}</ref> Moore wrote this song with and Dan Couch.<ref>{{cite news|last=Conaway|first=Alanna|title=Kip Moore, \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 \u2013 Lyrics Uncovered|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck-lyrics/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|newspaper=Taste of Country|date=September 18, 2011}}</ref> It garnered positive reviews from critics who praised Moore's delivery for being able to elevate generic lyrics.\n\n\"Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\" reached number one on the US [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] [[Hot Country Songs]] chart, the only single in Moore's career to reach that peak to date. It also gave him his first and only top 40 hit on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], peaking at number 29. The song was [[RIAA certification|certified 2x Platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA), denoting sales of over two million units in the country. It also charted in Canada, peaking at number 33 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]].\n\nTwo accompanying music videos were made for the single, the official version by Roger Pistole and an acoustic version by Stephen Shepherd.\n\n==Content==\nMoore discussed the album in an interview with [[American Songwriter]]. He stated, \"I made a conscious effort on this record to try to capture the youthful spirit that we all have inside of us. So often people as they get older they feel like things have to change inside their spirit. We all have to mature and take on different responsibilities. I tried to really capture...that you don\u2019t have to let your soul die or spirit die. You can still keep that youthful way and still live that way.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Behind The Wheel: A Q&A With Kip Moore|url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2012/06/behind-the-wheel-a-qa-with-kip-moore/2/|last=Jewly|first=Jewly|publisher=[[American Songwriter]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe song is in a moderate tempo in the key of [[B major]]. Its accompaniment is [[open fifth]]s instead of chords, in a pattern of B5-E5-B5-F{{sharp}}5-B5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/scorchVPE.asp?ppn=SC0238407&|title='Somethin' 'Bout a Truck' sheet music|publisher=MusicNotes.com|accessdate=July 3, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nBilly Dukes of ''[[Taste of Country]]'' gave the song three stars out of five, saying that \"vocally, he's not a perfect match for this style, but he's able to overcome somewhat cliche lyrics to create a memorable single.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Dukes|first=Billy|title=Kip Moore, \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 \u2013 Song Review|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Taste of Country|date=September 13, 2011}}</ref> Kevin John Coyne of Country Universe gave the song a B+ grade, writing that Moore \"sounds like he's reveling in the pleasures that await him at the end of the week after forty hours at the factory,\" calling it \"a welcome change from those who sound like high schoolers who hit up that back country road on their way home from the mall.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Coyne|first=Kevin John|title=Single Review: Kip Moore, \"Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\"|url=http://www.countryuniverse.net/2012/01/22/single-review-kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Roughstock|date=January 22, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was directed by Roger Pistole and premiered in October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Dukes|first=Billy|title=Kip Moore Releases Simple and Sexy \u2018Somethin\u2019 \u2018Bout a Truck\u2019 Video|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/kip-moore-somethin-bout-a-truck-video/|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Taste of Country|date=October 25, 2011}}</ref> An acoustic music video was directed by Stephen Shepherd and premiered in June 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/kip-moore/742541/somethin-bout-a-truck-acoustic.jhtml|title=CMT : Videos : Kip Moore : Somethin' 'Bout A Truck (Acoustic)|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|accessdate=August 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Somethin' 'Bout a Truck\" debuted at number 51 on the U.S. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Country Songs]] chart for the week of October 22, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Morris|first=Edward|title=Scotty McCreery, Keith Urban Top This Week's Album, Songs Charts|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1672552/scotty-mccreery-keith-urban-top-this-weeks-album-songs-charts.jhtml|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|date=October 15, 2011}}</ref> It also debuted at number 89 on the U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100]] chart for the week of February 25, 2012. It also debuted at number 97 on [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart for the week of April 14, 2012.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2011\u201312)\n!align=\"center\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|33|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|29|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcountrysongs|1|artist=Kip Moore|artistid=1639640}}\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2012)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/hot-100-songs?begin=91&order=position|title=Best of 2012 - Hot 100 Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|96\n|-\n| US [[Hot Country Songs|Country Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/hot-country-songs | title=Best of 2012: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 12\n|-\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United States|artist=Kip Moore|title=Somethin%27 Bout a Truck|award=Platinum|number=2|certyear=2014|certmonth=12|relyear=2011|access-date=March 21, 2015}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kip Moore}}\n\n[[Category:2011 singles]]\n[[Category:2011 songs]]\n[[Category:Kip Moore songs]]\n[[Category:MCA Nashville Records singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Country Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Brett James]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kip Moore]]\n[[Category:Songs about cars]]\n", "name_user": "DepressedPer", "label": "safe", "comment": "C/E Lead.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somethin%27_%27Bout_a_Truck"}
